Model evaluation

Model evaluation without cross-validation

Model evaluation computed only with the training dataset.

# read records
presences <- read.csv("Data/dataBases/Paramuricea_clavata.csv", sep = ";")
presences <- presences[, c("Lon", "Lat")]

# load layers of sea surface temperatures
envCond <- load_layers(c("BO2_tempmin_bdmean", "BO2_tempmax_bdmean"))

# crop layers to the European extent
europeanExtent <- extent(-15, 40, 25, 50)
envCond <- crop(envCond, europeanExtent)

# generate pseudo absences
absences <- pseudoAbsences(envCond, presences, n = 10000)
S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# extract environmental values and make a data.frame with PA information
modelData <- prepareModelData(presences, absences, envCond)

# fit a BRT model to the dataset
model <- train("BRT", modelData, folds = NULL)

# determine threshold dependent indices (assumes 0.5)
getAccuracy(model)
##   threshold       tss sensitivity specificity
## 1       0.5 0.5340921   0.5358852   0.9982069
S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# determine threshold dependent indices (low threshold retrieve high sensitivity)
getAccuracy(model, threshold = 0.1)
##   threshold       tss sensitivity specificity
## 1       0.1 0.8666807   0.8947368   0.9719439
# determine threshold dependent indices (high threshold retrieve low sensitivity)
getAccuracy(model, threshold = 0.9)
##   threshold tss sensitivity specificity
## 1       0.9   0           0           1
S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# plot the threshold-independent Receiver operating characteristic
plotROC(model)

# determine the threshold-independent AUC
getAUC(model)
## [1] 0.9834693

Model evaluation with cross-validation

Model evaluation computed with a proper test dataset.

# Cross validation with random partitioning of 10 folds
folds <- randomFolds(modelData, k = 10)

# fit a BRT model to the dataset
model <- train("BRT", modelData, folds = folds)

# determine AUC
getAUC(model, test = TRUE)
## [1] 0.9731287
S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# Cross validation with 4 blocks partitioning
folds2 <- get.block(presences, absences)

# fit a BRT model to the dataset
model <- train("BRT", modelData, folds = folds2)

# determine AUC
getAUC(model, test = TRUE)
## [1] 0.9529034

Reclassify predictive models

Use threshold dependent model evaluation to reclassify predictive surfaces

# predict with BRT to raster stack
map <- predict(model, envCond, type = c("logistic"))
plot(map, main = "Predictive model")

S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# determine the threshold maximizing the sum of sensitivity and specificity
threshold <- thresholdMaxTSS(model)

threshold
## [1] 0.08
S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# determine model performance
getAccuracy(model, threshold = threshold)
##   threshold      tss sensitivity specificity
## 1      0.08 0.888044   0.9282297   0.9598144
getAUC(model, test = TRUE)
## [1] 0.9529034
# generate a reclassification table
reclassMatrix <- data.frame(from = c(0, threshold), to = c(threshold, 1), value = c(0, 1))
reclassMatrix
##   from   to value
## 1 0.00 0.08     0
## 2 0.08 1.00     1
S7 // Predictive performance in Ecological Modelling

# apply threshold to reclassify the predictive surface
map <- reclassify(map, rcl = reclassMatrix)
plot(map, main = "Reclassified predictive model")

# change layer names for them to match
